# Schema Hardening — Cursor Implementation Prompt

You are hardening a production Prisma schema for a real consumer-facing meal prep business. A chef fulfills weekly orders; customers can customize meals with substitutions, modifiers, and protein boosts. Real money is processed via Stripe.

Read the full codebase before making any changes. Understand existing query patterns, API routes, and how `substitutions`, `modifiers`, and `proteinBoost` are currently read and written before touching anything. Do not break existing functionality.

Implement the changes below in priority order. For each change, create a Prisma migration and update all affected application code (API routes, server actions, queries, type definitions). After all changes, run `prisma validate` and confirm the schema is valid.

